==English==

===Etymology===
Greek nazarhne (Gospel of Mark 1:24) adjectival form of Aramaic clan name [[Nazar]] meaning ''sprig''.

===Proper noun===
'''Nazarene'''

# A person from [[Nazar]] or of Nazarene descent.
#:'''Translations'''
#:*Greek nazarhnoV (Mark 10:47)

===Adjective===
'''Nazarene'''

# Of, from, or pertaining to Nazara, the Nazarene community or the Nazarene dialect.

